  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Remote learning in rural Kenya for 1,000 children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">When COVID19 stops schools reopening what happens to the children?   In Kericho County, Kenya the children are working in the fields, collecting water and firewood, vulnerable, tired, hungry and open to exploitation.  They are losing out on their childhood, losing out on learning.  This project will change that by supporting community based learning groups to bring children together in small groups where they can learn, thrive and be safe for part of everyday.</narrative>
  </description>
